description:
A security scan identified an open redirect vulnerability in the Salesforce OAuth callback flow. The `retURL` parameter in the authentication redirect could potentially be manipulated to redirect users to malicious sites.

## OWASP Classification

Open redirects are an OWASP Top Ten vulnerability. They occur when an application allows user-supplied input to control offsite redirects, enabling phishing or spam attacks.

## Fix

Implement a domain validation function that checks whether the `instance_url` returned from Salesforce belongs to the `salesforce.com` domain before proceeding with authorization. If the domain doesn't match, redirect the user to an error page with an 'Invalid Salesforce domain' message.

```php
private function isValidSalesforceDomain($instanceUrl) {
    $expectedDomain = 'salesforce.com';
    return strpos($instanceUrl, $expectedDomain) !== false;
}
```
